Subject: Amanda--& The Blue Oblivion

On Tuesday, Amanda showed up Phoenix after traveling from Willcox,
AridZona--And before that-- Amanda was living in her 1966 Sundial for some 2
years this June traveling throughout the States--Wednesday Amanda adjusted
valves--changed oil--replaced cap and rotor--topped up tranny--So far the
bus is running fairly good-- Tranny was replaced in El Paso by Josh from the
Type II listing--Amanda will leaving Phoenix on Thursday for Yucaipa,
California--Be looking for a Blue splittie on I-10 heading West--
Amanda says hello and thanks to everyone on the AIRS list and all the
friendly VW Bus people along the way-
Recently in Austin, Texas, Amanda visited Big Bend National Park, and La
Kiva a most Friendly "Place of Spirits: no VW People--But the most fun since
Mardis Gras !! Again thanks to all and I will be on "The Golden Road"
soon--
Amanda--
